# Project: Inbox AI

## Stack
- Next.js 14 with App Router and TypeScript
- Supabase (Postgres + auth)
- pgvector for embeddings
- NextAuth.js for Google OAuth
- Anthropic SDK for Claude
- OpenAI SDK for embeddings only
- Inngest for background jobs
- Tailwind CSS for styling, shadcn/ui for components

## Conventions
- All API routes under /app/api, use Route Handlers (not pages/api)
- All database access goes through /lib/db/, never inline SQL in components
- All Gmail API calls go through /lib/gmail.ts wrapper
- Use Zod for input validation on all API routes
- Errors: throw typed errors with descriptive messages, log via console.error, return user-friendly messages to UI
- Never log email body content; log only metadata (message ID, user ID, action)
- All async operations use async/await, never .then chains
- Components: prefer server components, mark client components explicitly with 'use client'

## File structure
/app
  /api
    /auth/[...nextauth]
    /sync (start sync)
    /search (query endpoint)
    /threads/[id] (thread detail)
  /(app)
    /search (main app page)
    /thread/[id] (thread detail page)
  /landing (logged-out home)
/lib
  /db (database client and queries)
  /gmail.ts (Gmail API wrapper)
  /llm.ts (Claude wrapper)
  /embeddings.ts (OpenAI wrapper)
/inngest
  /sync.ts (background sync job)

## Security non-negotiables
- Encrypt refresh tokens before storing
- Use Supabase RLS policies on all tables
- All user-data queries must include user_id filter
- Never expose Gmail message bodies in API responses to users other than the owner
